r than staying contextual, which would break any code using it as a method name. The solution would be to either escape it with `@with` or rename the method entirely.","outputTokens":5215,"requestId":"886B:A067E:1CF6BA7:205B1D7:69FA9B31"},"id":"aec69932-ccaf-483f-b714-f4d883133269","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:38:48.153Z","parentId":"cb6bd2f6-ffba-4262-9a0a-384866948244"}
